The 1961 Ferrari 250 GT SWB California Spider is regarded by many as the most beautiful convertible ever made . 
  It was used as the car in the famous scene in the 1986 film Ferris Bueller's Day Off . 
  The car was driven by the father of Ferris' best friend Cameron in the movie . 
  But in the film the car crashed into a ravine after Cameron accidentally knocked it off the jack . 
  It is almost identical to the model driven in the classic film and is expected to sell for £10million at auction . 
  It will be sold next month at RM Sotheby's auction in Villa Erba, Italy . 
